Question 1.1.12

Function: f(x^k) -> f(x*)   ||x^k-x*|| < d

a) Proving x* is locally stable: lim(k->inf)f(x^k) = f(x*)
                                 lim(k->inf)f(x^k) - f(x*) = 0 < d

b) Function: f(x)+E*g(x), where E>0
     
   Proving strict local minimum: f(x)-E*const <= f(x)+E*g(x) <= f(x)+E*const
                                 If f(x)+E*const describes radius of a sphere from minimum (x*),
                                 then f(x)-E*g(x) decreases as f(x)+E*const reduces. 



Rules: Stability Analysis vs Sensitivy Analysis
       
       Stability Analysis:
                          
                           Descrption: optimal solutions when perturbations radically change the minimum
       Sensitivy Analysis: minimize f(x,a)
                           subject to x|Real Number
                           delx(a)=-del_x*del_a[f(x(a),a)]/(del_x*del_x[f(x(a),a))
